longBusinessSummary: Dr. HÃ¶nle AG supplies industrial UV technologies worldwide. It operates through three segments: Equipment & Systems, Glass & Lamps, and Adhesives. The Equipment & Systems segment offers LED UV units, UV equipment/UV systems/UV units, IR units, inert systems, UV disinfection systems, solar simulation systems and light fixtures, lighting systems, UV measuring technology products, and components and replacement parts. This segment also provides UVC air disinfection, water disinfection, and surface disinfection products; ozone odor removal products; sheet-fed offset printing products; drying, and powder spraying and extraction systems; UV/UV inert/IR/TL technology products; hot air dryers; UV LEDs; coating solutions; UV systems; and special water treatment plants. Its products are used for drying inks and coatings, curing adhesives and plastics, disinfecting surfaces, and solar simulation. The Glass & Lamps segment offers UV low and medium pressure lamps, infrared emitters, electronic power supplies; UV sensors and measuring technology products; UV measuring devices; submersible and immersion tube systems; quartz glass and quartz glass components, as well as accessories. The Adhesives segment offers industrial, UV, medical grade, and conductive adhesives; UV equipment; dosing systems; potting and sealing compounds; and UV curing units. Dr. HÃ¶nle AG was founded in 1976 and is headquartered in GrÃ¤felfing, Germany.
